  %section
    %h2 Text Editor What What?
    :markdown
      Sublime Text 2, that you downloaded at the beginning, is your
      **text editor**.  When HTMLdog says stuff about Notepad,
      just use Sublime instead.

      <small>It's **soooo much better** than Notepad!</small>

  %section
    %h2 Oh, &amp; yes, Sublime costs money
    :markdown
      That is, it will prompt for you to buy a full copy every 10
      saves or so. It's kind of expensive, and there are free
      alternatives (they're just usually not as pretty), so you
      need not feel bad for taking it for a long test drive.
      You should probably try some of the free alternatives before
      you spring to buy it.

