  %section
    %h2 Rummaging through someone else's HTML
    :markdown
      In Chrome (you are using Chrome for this presentation, aren't you?)
      right-click this word and select "Inspect Element" from
      the context menu.

  %section
    %h2 The text is in a &lt;p&gt; tag!
    :markdown
      You'll learn what that means as you go through HTMLdog. You can do
      this on any website. You can even right-click elements in the
      Inspector and _edit_ them! Try it now! Make the previous heading say
      "Rummaging through someone else's _markup_". Don't
      worry, you won't mess up the site.  Just refresh the page &amp; it
      will be as good as new.  Can you figure out why? (Think about the
      play we did.)

